      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's a frustrating feeling, and you're right, it can feel like the interest is running a sneaky campaign against your budget! Sometimes, the perceived \"hidden costs\" are actually just the mechanics of how loans are structured, but other factors can definitely make it feel worse. For instance, if you have a very long repayment term, the initial interest accrual is higher because the principal balance stays high for so long. Also, if your interest rate is variable, and it goes up, that interest chunk—the part that eats your payment—will immediately get bigger, making it feel like the loan is suddenly growing on you.",
